{"key":"post-17926131","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>17926131</id>\n<content>Fungus gnats breed in your houseplants, especially during winter.&amp;nbsp; Find out which one and use a shop-vac to get all the loose topsoil off, which takes most of the gnats and eggs with it.&amp;nbsp; Then, pour 3% peroxide over the soil to saturate it and run out the bottom.&amp;nbsp; This will kill the gnat larvae.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Finally, replace the soil you vacuumed off with fresh potting soil.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;They won't breed in your substrates unless they're too wet and won't colonize.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>17926203</next>\n<prev>17926104</prev>\n<first>17925217</first>\n<last>17926203</last>\n<when>1362797117</when>\n<utime>03/09/13 04:45 AM</utime>\n</post>"}